                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240218-117-off655 t18240218-117-crimeloc657"></join>. On the 7th of February, at half-past seven o'clock in the evening, I was behind the counter, and saw the prisoner come and take a pair of stockings which hung just inside the door - he ran off; I followed, and took him three hundred yards off - and the watchman picked them up. I never lost sight of him, but did not see them thrown away.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240218-117-person1166">
                  PETER 
                  MARTIN
